    • Method Detail

      • onTimeout

        protected void onTimeout()
        Description copied from class: MessageDecorator
        Triggered when the decorator times out. If this method isn't overridden, it will throw an exception but this method isn't called by default.

        On the other hand, an implementation like ReactionDecorator will call MessageDecorator.destroy() on timeout which is an expected behaviour.

        Overrides:
        onTimeout in class SafeAutoDestroyDisposableReactionDecorator
